President Obama spoke with Turkish President Recep Tayyip Erdogan about the situation in Syria and the need to continue efforts to defeat ISIS and disrupt its ability to carry out terrorist operations. They also discussed the importance of international cooperation to maintain a ceasefire and make progress on a political transition in Syria. The two leaders also talked about the possibility of increased cooperation in the fight against all terrorist groups, including the PKK. President Obama reiterated the United States' commitment to Turkey's security as a NATO ally.